title: Experimental study of the excitation functions of proton induced reactions on natural Sn up to 65 MeV

x4freetext: Experimental study of the excitation functions of
proton induced reactions on natural Sn up to 65 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.247, p.180 (2006)
Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data for Sci.and Techn., Santa Fe 2004, Vol.2, p.1662 (2004)

x4freetext: Preliminary data.
Natural high purity (>99%) Sn foils from Goodfellow.
Thicknesses: 55.39 micron in Brussels,
15 micron in Sendai.
Three stacks were irradiated.
The energies of the proton beams: 32 MeV (Brussels)
and 70 MeV (two stacks, Sendai),
the beam intensity: 200 nA,
the irradiation times: 30-60 min.
Faraday-cup like or isolated target holder were used.
Nondestructive measurement without chemical separation.
Measurements were repeated several times for eight
weeks after the end of bombardment.
Stopping and energy degradation were calculated using
the Andersen-Ziegler polynomial approximation.
Decay data were taken from NuDat database.
Thicknesses of monitor foils:
99.21 micron Al and 25.77 and 12 micron Ti in Brussels,
500 and 1000 micron Al and 54 micron Cu in Sendai.
Chapter 4

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.188, p.106 (2002)

x4freetext: Taking into account the cumulative effects of
possible incident energy variation and thickness of
the different targets, the uncertainty of the median
energy in the last foil is 2 MeV in Brussels
and 5 MeV in Sendai.
The following individual uncertainties are
included in the propagated error calculation:
* the number of target nuclei including
non-uniformity (3%),
* incident particle intensity (5%),
* detection efficiency (5%),
* determination of the peak areas
including statistical errors (1-5%) and
* absolute abundance of the used gamma-rays (1-5%).
The total resulting uncertainty was obtained by
quadratic summation of the contributing sources.
The strongly non-linear effect of the possible
uncertainty of the half-lives was not taken into
account.
The measured experimental data were compared to
those found in the literature.
The measured experimental data were compared to
and analyzed with theoretical calculations based on
the model code ALICE-IPPE.
On the basis of the new experimental cross
sections integral yields were calculated.

124m2Sb decays totally to the ground state.
Includes contribution from the metastable
state after its total decay.

x4freetext: Independent because 110Sn and the metastable state do
not decay to this ground state.
Includes contribution from 109Sb, 109Sn and
109mIn (100% isomeric transition) after their

Compiler`s comment: contradiction between the ref.
and NuDat database regarding the half-lives of
isomeric states of 110In. NuDat says that half-life of
the ground state is 4.90 h and half-life of the
metastable state is 1.15 h.
The reaction product is given by the compiler as
ground state in accordance with NuDat and in contrast
with the ref.
